<section
  class="form-content tab {{#if tab.active}} active{{/if}}" data-group="{{tab.group}}" data-tab="{{tab.id}}"
>
  <h4>
    <i class="fas fa-user"></i> {{localize "CRLNGN_UI.ui.clientSettingsLabel"}} <span class="toggle-hint">{{localize 'CRLNGN_UI.ui.toggleHints'}}</span>
  </h4>
  <hr/>

  <p class="hint">{{localize "CRLNGN_UI.settings.playersListMenu.hint"}}</p>

  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="autoHidePlayerList">{{fields.autoHidePlayerList.label}}</label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="autoHidePlayerList" {{#if autoHidePlayerList}}checked{{/if}} />
    <p class="hint">{{fields.autoHidePlayersList.hint}}</p> 
  </div>

  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="playerListAvatars">{{fields.playerListAvatars.label}}</label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="playerListAvatars" {{#if playerListAvatars}}checked{{/if}} />
    <p class="hint">{{fields.playerListAvatars.hint}}</p>
  </div>
</section>

<p>News for version 2.1.4:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Fade Out Control:</b> Ability to enable or disable fade out behavior of interface elements individually.</li>
  <li><b>Interface customization:</b> Foundry v13 looks nicer, and not everyone wants to use all elements from Carolingian UI. Now, you can enable/disable each part of the interface individually. Don't want to change the macro layout or sidebar tabs? Go ahead and disable it!</li>
  <li><b>Reworked Scene Navigation:</b> Use the folder toggle on horizontal Scene Nav to navigate on your folders directly in scene nav Folder Navigation; Active / Viewed scenes are now separated as it's Foundry's default;</li>
  <li><b>Shortcuts on Scene Preview:</b> View and toggle global illumination, token vision and scene sound from preview</li>
  <li><b>Toggle Floating chat box:</b> Button to hide/show the chat input box</li>
  <li><b>Players List avatars:</b> show miniature images of each player in Players List</li>
</ul>
